From: Xiang Yang <xiangyang3@huawei.com>
Date: Sat, 12 Aug 2023 14:27:48 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/exynos: fix a potential error pointer dereference
Git-commit: 73bf1c9ae6c054c53b8e84452c5e46f86dd28246
Patch-mainline: v6.7-rc5
References: git-fixes

Smatch reports the warning below:
drivers/gpu/drm/exynos/exynos_hdmi.c:1864 hdmi_bind()
Error: 'crtc' dereferencing possible ERR_PTR()

The return value of exynos_drm_crtc_get_by_type maybe ERR_PTR(-ENODEV),
which can not be used directly. Fix this by checking the return value
before using it.

Signed-off-by: Xiang Yang <xiangyang3@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Inki Dae <inki.dae@samsung.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/exynos/exynos_hdmi.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/exynos/exynos_hdmi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/exynos/exynos_hdmi.c
index f3aaa4ea3e68..dd9903eab563 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/exynos/exynos_hdmi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/exynos/exynos_hdmi.c
@@ -1861,6 +1861,8 @@ static int hdmi_bind(struct device *dev, struct device *master, void *data)
 		return ret;
 
 	crtc = exynos_drm_crtc_get_by_type(drm_dev, EXYNOS_DISPLAY_TYPE_HDMI);
+	if (IS_ERR(crtc))
+		return PTR_ERR(crtc);
 	crtc->pipe_clk = &hdata->phy_clk;
 
 	ret = hdmi_create_connector(encoder);
